Hey <%= @user.fullname %>,
<p>
  We're always hard at work to become the most awesome community for software developers. That's what we have done for you lately:
</p>
<ul>
  <li>
    <b>New detail pages:</b> We reworked our detail pages completely. You can see the most important KPI's on the right side with a color coded ranking. These numbers are helping you to make decisions. Read more here: <a href="http://versioneye.wordpress.com/2013/09/12/kpis-for-software-libraries/">KPIs for software libraries</a>
    <br/><br/>
    <a href="http://versioneye.wordpress.com/2013/09/12/kpis-for-software-libraries/"><img src="http://versioneye.files.wordpress.com/2013/09/kpis.png" width="200" /></a>
    <br/><br/>
  </li>
  <li>
    <b>Collaborators:</b> You can add collaborators to your project now. They will get email notifications as well. Read more here: <a href="http://versioneye.wordpress.com/2013/09/12/versioneye-collaborators/">VersionEye collaborators</a>
    <br/><br/>
  </li>
  <li>
    <b>ALL repo switch:</b> So far we only supported repositories from languages VersionEye already supports. We just changed that. The "switch" widget is always active now and we try to find a project file we can parse. Read more here: <a href="http://versioneye.wordpress.com/2013/09/12/switch-for-all-repos/">Switch for all repos</a>
    <br/><br/>
  </li>
  <li>
    <b>New statistic page:</b> We reworked the statistic page as well with D3. Check it out here: <a href="http://www.versioneye.com/statistics">http://www.versioneye.com/statistics</a>
    <br/><br/>
  </li>
  <li>
    <b>Life filter for GitHub repos:</b> Because some of you guys have more than 1000 repositories on GitHub we added a life search field to our GitHub Single Page App.
    <br/><br/>
  </li>
</ul>
<p>
